address: Jl. Serma Arda No.1, Bajera, Kec. Selemadeg, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82162, Indonesia
review 1:
Im not the biggest bakso fan, but i do like mie ayam bakso and even better is the mie ayam iga bakso or just iga bakso served here.
Has a nice juicy beef rib encased in the bakso meat ball. So good i cannot wait to drive by again and stop for a quick delicious snack/meal.
They even have way out there ideas such as:
Bakso keju mozzarella
And bakso chocolate (hmmm ill try that next time)
Fast, friendly service and a clean restaurant space (cannot be said for many bakso restaurants unfirtoturnatly)

name: Warung Nasi Mulia
address: Jl. Ngurah Rai No.35, Bajera, Kec. Selemadeg, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82162, Indonesia
review 1:
This small stall, located at the South end of the Bajera market terminal, has been around since the 70s.
It started as a humble street vendor and has since become a hidden gem that serves delicious nasi campur and soto.

Despite its simple menu, the flavors are amazing and the prices are reasonable. For less than 25 thousand rupiah, you can enjoy a portion of Nasi Campur with side dishes of meat, soto, and a refreshing glass of iced orange.

The side dish menu changes every day, but babi nyat nyat, soto, and the jerky ‚Äì these are my personal favorites.

One downside to this otherwise great experience is that the food ordering system can be disorganized. Be sure to repeat your order to avoid any misunderstandings with the waiters.
review 2:
Balinese cuisine, suckling pig and pork soup so delicious..not too expensive, still in a very reasonable prices...must visit..very recommended
Located in Bajra traditional market
